Second failure had a different root cause: the remote machine had a stale saved customisation of `flycheck-haskell-runghc-command` (the old short form without `-packageCabal` flags). Without those flags GHC has no Cabal package in scope during CPP, so `MIN_VERSION_Cabal` is never defined and all version guards silently fall through to the oldest pre-Cabal-2.0 branches, which fail against Cabal 3.14.

Fix added to `warbo-haskell.el` `:config`: `(unless (member "-packageCabal" flycheck-haskell-runghc-command) (custom-reevaluate-setting 'flycheck-haskell-runghc-command))`. This resets any stale saved customisation to the current computed default (which includes the necessary `-packageCabal` flags) without affecting machines that have the correct value.
